# BriefScope LOCAL GPU — environment variables
#
# Prerequisites:
#   1. NVIDIA GPU in the host machine
#   2. NVIDIA Container Toolkit installed:
#      https://docs.nvidia.com/datacenter/cloud-native/container-toolkit/install-guide.html
#
# The model is downloaded automatically on first start.
# GPU-capable recommended models (sorted by VRAM):
#   llama3.2        ~2 GB VRAM  — fast, good quality          (default)
#   phi4-mini       ~2.5 GB     — Microsoft, very capable
#   mistral         ~4 GB       — strong reasoning
#   deepseek-r1:7b  ~4 GB       — great for document analysis
#   llama3.1:70b    ~40 GB      — max quality (needs high-end GPU)
OLLAMA_MODEL=llama3.2

# Embedding model for document search (RAG). Computed by the bundled Ollama
# server (no sentence-transformers/torch); pulled into Ollama automatically on
# first use, and GPU-accelerated automatically. Also selectable from the UI.
# NOTE: changing it invalidates previously indexed documents — re-upload them so
# they are re-embedded with the new model.
# Recommended embedding models (sorted by size):
#   nomic-embed-text       ~137 MB  — best for CPU, 8192-token context  (default)
#   mxbai-embed-large      ~334 MB  — high-quality English retrieval (recommended)
#   bge-m3                 ~568 MB  — multilingual (100+ languages, incl. Spanish)
#   qwen3-embedding        ~639 MB  — low-memory / edge devices
EMBEDDING_MODEL=nomic-embed-text

# These are set automatically by docker-compose — do not change:
# ROOT_PATH=/api/briefscope_local_gpu
# LLM_MODE=local
# OLLAMA_HOST=http://briefscope_ollama_gpu:11434
